value.value: A skeletal muscle fiber found in an embryo. In mammalian embryos, skeletal muscle expresses myosin heavy chain-embryonic (MyHC-emb, encoded by the MYH3 gene), which regulates skeletal muscle development.

A fibroblast located in the portal triad. Hepatic portal fibroblast are a non-parenchymal cell population located adjacent to bile duct epithelia in liver and are distinct from stellate cells. They differentiate into fibrogenic myofibroblasts during chronic injury states producing high levels of collagen.

label.value: lymph node lymphatic vessel endothelial cell

value.value: An endothelial cell located in a lymph node lymphatic vessel.

label.value: progenitor cell of mammary luminal epithelium

value.value: A progenitor cell with the potential to differentiate into luminal epithelial cells of mammary glands. In mouse, CD61 and c-kit were found to be coexpressed by the majority of, but not all, committed luminal progenitor cells.

definition.value: A stromal cell that is part_of a bone marrow.
An epithelial cell that is part_of a umbilical artery.

label.value: epithelial cell of alveolus of lung

definition.value: An epithelial cell that is part_of a alveolus of lung.
May be merged with pneumocyte in future
A mononuclear cell that is part_of a bone marrow.

value.value: Any blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of some heart.
Any endothelial cell that is part of some heart.
Any photoreceptor cell that is part of some camera-type eye.
A GABAergic interneuron whose soma is located in the cerebral cortex.
A CNS neuron of the cerebral cortex.

definition.value: A zygote in a plant or an animal.

value.value: Any glial cell that is part of some heart.
Any myoblast that develops into some cardiac muscle cell.
A neuron that has its soma in the heart.

definition.value: This term is used in 3 GO terms that were created as part of the heart development focus project.

value.value: A motor neuron that passes from the spinal cord toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.
An interneuron that uses GABA as a vesicular neurotransmitter.  These interneurons are inhibitory

definition.value: The formal and textual definitions of this term will need to be altered if evidence for non-inhibitory GABA-ergic neurons emerges.

value.value: A cell in the area of mesoderm in the neurulating embryo that flanks and forms simultaneously with the neural tube. The cells of this region give rise to somites.

A cell of the neural crest. Neural crest cells are multipotent. Premigratory neural crest cells are found at the neural plate boarder, some of which will undergo ectomesynchymal transition and delamination to form migratory neural crest cells.
A sperm cell that is cabaple of motion (motility).
A motile sperm cell that contains a slender threadlike microscopic appendage that enables motion.

definition.value: A mesothelial cell that is part of the epicardium.
A fibroblast that is part of upper back skin.
A fibroblast that is part of skin of back.

value.value: A double negative thymocyte that is CD3-positive, CD4-negative, CD8-negative, that that are present in the periphery in very low numbers and predominantly produce INF-gamma, TNF-alpha, and a low amount of TGF-beta, but not IL-2, IL-4, IL-10 or IL-13 upon activation.
An effector T cell that displays impaired effector functions (e.g., rapid production of effector cytokines, cytotoxicity) and has limited proliferative potential.

A precursor cell that has a tendency to differentiate into a specific type of cell. They are descendants of stem cells, only they are more constrained in their differentiation potential or capacity for self-renewal, and are often more limited in both senses.
Any fibroblast that is part of skeletal muscle tissue.
Any microvascular endothelial cell that is part of the dermis.

Cells of the uterine chorion that acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize chorionic trophoblasts. These cells will migrate towards the spongiotrophoblast layer and give rise to syncytiotrophoblasts of the labyrinthine layer.
Epithelial cell that is part of the colon epithelium.
Neuron found in the spiral ganglion.
A cell that, by division or terminal differentiation, can give rise to other cell types.

definition.value: Work is needed on GO 'cell differentiation' before it is clear whether the equivalent class definition 'native cell' that capable_of some 'cell differentiation' works. Also, may want to consider merging this with non-terminally differentiated cell.
A CNS neuron of the forebrain.

value.value: Any radial glial cell that is part of some forebrain.
A neuroendocrine cell that is part of the prostate epithelium.
Cytoplasm that exhibits a characteristic staining and color, pale-pink, with Wright-Giemsa stain.
Cytoplasm that exhibits a characteristic staining and color, red or pink, with Eosin stain.
Cytoplasm that exhibits molecular interaction for basic dyes under specific pH conditions.
Cytoplasm that exhibits affinity for both basic and acid stains under specific pH conditions.

definition.value: Any serous secreting cell that is part of the tracheobronchial epithelium.
Any chondrocyte that is part of the tracheobronchial tree.
Any goblet cell that is part of the tracheobronchial epithelium.

value.value: A smooth muscle cell that is part of any lymphatic vessel.
A smooth muscle cell that is part of any blood vessel.
A smooth muscle cell that is part of the tracheobronchial tree.

An epithelial cell of the extrahepatic bile ducts, including the left and right hepatic duct, common hepatic duct, and common bile duct. They are columnar in shape, and have a large nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ratio relative to small/intrahepatic cholangiocytes.
